data.value:
Main Form Script Buttons
"Set Up a New Computer" - runs setup scripts on local machine to set NIST policies and STIG requirements.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Enable Client Connections" - enables PSRemoting and adds remote hosts to trusted hosts on local machine to allow remote communication with MOB/MAR computers.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"CKL Clone" - generates 23 copies of a CKL file with incrementing host numbers.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"CKL Edit" - modifies the generated CKL copies or any CKL folder with the correct host information.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Remote Script" - executes scripts accesible on trial clients remotely. (Not commonly needed)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Remote Command" - remotely force runs a command on clients. (See remote command help for more information)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"**Power Off Hosts" - powers down clients selected in the checklist.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Client System Report" - generates a spreadsheet for selected batch with the following information:
ComputerName IPAddress OSName OSVersion Model Drive_Capacity_GB FreeSpace_Capacity_GB DefaultPrinter MachineInactivityLimit Battery_Health #FirewallMap Inbound_FireWall_Private Inbound_FireWall_Public Inbound_FireWall_Domain
